w:r.w:t: Training Manual: How to add same day appointment block to scheduler

By far the simplest and most universal way to add a same-day appointment block to the scheduler is to create a fake patient with a name such as “BLOCK for Same-Day Appointment.” Adding such blocks will remind the provider and staff to not schedule appointments within
unless the appointment is a same-day appointment. {{if not EMR_NAME=='
':}}The following instructions are shown using the popular EMR
, but the concept is applicable to virtually all EMRs including our own {{=EMR_NAME}}
•The first step to implementing the same-day block using this fake patient method is to create the fake patient. This only needs to be done once.

•The next step is to reserve the scheduler for same-day appointments using the fake patient, based on the policy of {{=PRACTICE_NAME}}. This should be done before or at the start of every work week! Here is an example of an ideal scheduler with the scheduler of the entire work week properly blocked for same-day appointments.
